The cylindrical cocoons, made with drier dark yellowish cerumen (darker at bottom), were about 5.8 mm high by 3.78 mm wide, while the cells, lighter and smoother, were a little more spherical (
Figs. 39, 40, 41, 43, 44
). Two cells were under construction (
Fig. 44
) and still without provisions. Open cells displayed liquid provisions and with eggs positioned vertically (
Fig. 40
).

